728131f-a.text:
Utopia Parkway at the S.E. corner of Seventy-third Ave. (formerly Fresh Meadow Lane at Black Stump Road), showing a small pond.
About 1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

725611f-a.text:
73rd Avenue, near Utopia Parkway, showing an old cemetery. Streets were later laid out here and the area developed into a residential neighborhood. 73rd Avenue is the former Black Stump
Road.
P. L. Sperr  March 31, 1927

728132f-a.text:
Utopia Parkway, east side, between 73rd and Jewel Avenues. showing Public School No. 26, formerly Public School No. 28.
P. L. Sperr March 31, 1927

728130f-b.text:
Utopia Parkway, east side, between 73rd and Jewel Avenues, show the low frame structure of the Black Stump Hook and Ladder Company No. 1. It is a former schoolhouse and was known as Black Stump School No. 4 from 1860 to 1891. Just north of this structure is Public School No. 26, the former Public School No. 28.
Views 1,2,3: Eugene L. Armbruster Collection View 1: 1922 Views 2,3: 1929
View 4: P. L. Sperr View 4: 1927
